  "prompt": "Has Quora become less popular?",
  "response": "Determining whether Quora has become less popular can depend on various metrics such as user engagement, traffic, and active users. Here are a few points to consider:\n\n1. **Traffic and User Engagement:**\n   - According to SimilarWeb, Quora's traffic has seen fluctuations over the years. As of the latest data, Quora still attracts millions of visitors monthly, but growth may have plateaued in some regions.\n   - Engagement metrics like time spent on the site and the number of questions and answers posted can also provide insight. Some users report a perceived decrease in the quality of content and engagement.\n\n2. **App Downloads and Usage:**\n   - Data from app analytics platforms like App Annie show that Quora's app downloads and usage have varied. While it remains a popular app, the growth rate might not be as high as in its earlier years.\n\n3. **\u7af6\u722d\u8207\u66ff\u4ee3\u65b9\u6848 (Competition and Alternatives):**\n   - The rise of other platforms like Reddit, Stack Exchange, and even social media sites like Twitter and LinkedIn, where users can ask and answer questions, may have impacted Quora's user base.\n   - Newer platforms and features on existing social media might attract users looking for different types of engagement and community.\n\n4. **User Feedback:**\n   - Anecdotal evidence from user forums and social media suggests that some long-time users feel that Quora's popularity has waned due to changes in the platform's algorithms, user interface, and content moderation policies.\n   - However, Quora still has a dedicated user base that actively participates and finds value in the platform.\n\n5. **Quora's Own Statements:**\n   - Quora's management has not publicly stated a decline in popularity. Instead, they often highlight new features and initiatives aimed at improving user experience and expanding their reach.\n\nIn summary, while Quora remains a significant player in the Q&A space, there are indications that its growth may have slowed and that it faces increased competition. Whether it has become \"less popular\" can be subjective and depends on which metrics and user experiences one considers.",
